<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="214" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,827,1538]" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,900,926]" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 16–17.1; head length: 1.9–2.0; head width: 3.1–3.2; pronotal length: 3.4–3.5; pronotal width: 10–10.3; scutellum length: 7.5–7.8; scutellum width: 5.8–6.0; abdominal width: 8.6–8.8; length of antennal segments. I: 1.0; II: 2.0–2.1; III: 1.2–1.5; IV: 4.7–5.0; V: missing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="214" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,827,1538]" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1007,1033]" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along all of its extension. Anterolateral margin punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with black punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1338,1043,1070]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777100/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 20I</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin concolorous (
<figureCitation box="[591,685,1079,1106]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777100/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 20I</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with dark brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1256,1079,1106]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777100/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 20J</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[159,300,1115,1142]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@28.[232,1355,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Hypoxys ventrotuberculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore;A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777094/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 17A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with dorsal rim sinuous, presenting a small median dark, rounded projection (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1424,1115,1142]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@28.[232,1355,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Hypoxys ventrotuberculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore;A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777094/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup oblong, narrow, ventral margin with two subtriangular small projections; process contiguous to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[708,848,1187,1214]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@28.[232,1355,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Hypoxys ventrotuberculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore;A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777094/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 17A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere with a large subtriangular and truncated lobe directed anteriorly; posterior lobe short and triangular; inner low carina splitting distally finishing at anterior and posterior apices (
<figureCitation box="[400,539,1259,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@28.[232,1355,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Hypoxys ventrotuberculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore;A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777094/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 17B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with laterodorsal tufts of long setae separated by narrow, sparsely setose ridge; posterior face pentagonal, upper part swollen (
<figureCitation box="[838,980,1295,1322]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@28.[232,1355,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Hypoxys ventrotuberculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore;A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777094/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 17A–D</figureCitation>
). Expansions of ventral rim acuminated and developed, far exceeding the level of the posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1202,1331,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@28.[232,1355,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Hypoxys ventrotuberculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore;A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777094/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 17D</figureCitation>
). Female (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1424,1331,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@28.[232,1355,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Hypoxys ventrotuberculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore;A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777094/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 17E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 wide, posterior margin sinuous; inner angles rounded and convergent reaching basal part of valvifers 9; inner margins with narrow and elliptic excavation. Valvulae 8 exposed. Valvifers 9 with low medial carina.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
